<article class="env-definition" id="00CK">
  <p><a class="environment-identifier" href="/tag/00CK">Definition <span data-tag="00CK">18.3.1</span>.</a> Let $\mathcal{C}$ be a fusion category. Its Grothendieck group $\mathbf{Gr}(\mathcal{C})$ is the abelian group freely generated by isomorphism classes of simple objects. We define, for an object $X\in \mathcal{C}$, its class $[X]\in \mathbf{Gr}(\mathcal{C})$ by </p>
  <div class="equation">
  \[  [X]=\sum _{i\in \mathcal{O}(\mathcal{C})} [X:X_ i] [X_ i].  \]
</div>
</article>